The paper focuses on human-robot collaboration for a pick-up task, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) category. The proposed method involves natural language processing and understanding user commands, which suggests a connection to the natural language processing (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The interaction with the human user also implies a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the use of computer vision to estimate the position of the object may also suggest a connection to computer vision (cs.CV).
